text: Moritz is an unincorporated community in Deuel County, in the U.S. state of South Dakota. ==History== A post office called Moritz was established in 1899, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1923. The community was named for Andrew Moritz, an early settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Deuel County, South Dakota Category:Unincorporated communities in South Dakota
title: Moritz, South Dakota
